    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "## Summary\n\nNeovim contains a use-after-free vulnerability (CVE-2025-26603) inherited from Vim in the register display code. When redirecting `:display` output to a register, the code attempts to skip the register being written to (to avoid UAF), but the check is incomplete — it only handles the `\"` register, not `*` and `+` clipboard registers which can alias to the same yank buffer.\n\n## Vulnerability Details\n\n- **CVE**: [CVE-2025-26603](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-26603)\n- **Type**: Use-After-Free (CWE-416)\n- **Affected File**: `src/nvim/register.c`, lines 2151-2152\n- **Root Cause**: Incomplete register aliasing check in `ex_display()`\n\n## Vulnerable Code\n\n```c\n// src/nvim/register.c:2151-2152 (current Neovim)\nif (name == mb_tolower(redir_reg)\n    || (redir_reg == '\"' && yb == y_previous)) {\n    continue;\n}\n```\n\nThis only checks `redir_reg == '\"'` but does NOT check `*` and `+` registers.\n\n## Recommended Fix\n\nApply the Vim fix (patch 9.1.1115, [vim/vim@c0f0e238](https://github.com/vim/vim/commit/c0f0e2380e59)):\n\nExtend the check to include `*` and `+` registers and also check against `y_regs[0]`.\n\n## References\n\n- Vim fix: https://github.com/vim/vim/commit/c0f0e2380e59\n- CVE: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-26603\n- Verified on Neovim v0.13.0-dev (latest master, commit 9c5fba5)\n",
