            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thank you @zeertzjq for pointing out the dependency on #31936.\n\nYou are right — the CVE-2025-26603 UAF requires the `*` and `+` registers to properly alias with the yank buffer (`y_previous` / `y_regs[0]`). Since Neovim's clipboard provider integration (#31936) does not currently create this aliasing condition, the UAF trigger path is effectively blocked.\n\nI apologize for the incorrect report. The static code pattern matched the Vim vulnerability, but I did not account for Neovim's different clipboard register implementation that prevents the precondition from being met.\n\nThank you for the thorough review.",
